) is futile. Only he who is =\r\nfree from egoistic and volitional activity and who is utterly non-attached =\r\nto anything here, is genuinely liberated&quot;. \n&gt; \n&gt; As Lord Krishna says in th=\r\ne Gita, \n&gt; \n&gt; &quot;56. He whose mind is not shaken by adversity, who does not h=\r\nanker after \n&gt; pleasures, and who is free from attachment, fear and anger, =\r\nis called a \n&gt; sage of steady wisdom.57. He who is everywhere without attac=\r\nhment, on meeting with anything good \n&gt; or bad, who neither rejoices nor ha=\r\ntes, his wisdom is fixed&quot;\n&gt; \n&gt; The same truth has been repeated thousands o=\r\nf times across scriptures and by different enlightened men across centuries=\r\n.=C3=82=C2=A0 Perfect equanimity in thoughts, words and deeds is the ultima=\r\nte goal to be attained. Any thing else, any mystical experience etc, is hel=\r\npful to the extent that it aids this goal. If however, a mystical experienc=\r\ne does not produce internal detachment and results in increasing pride (eve=\r\nn subconscious pride) it can prove detrimental in the final equation.\n&gt; \n&gt; =\r\n-Regards\n&gt; =C3=82=C2=A0Rajarshi\n&gt; \n&gt; \n&gt; \n&gt; From: Narasimha P.V.R. Rao &lt;pvr@=\r\n...&gt;\n&gt; To: Lalit Mishra &lt;litsol@...&gt;; AK Kaul &lt;jyotirved@...&gt;; &quot;freeflowaum=\r\n@...&quot; &lt;freeflowaum@...&gt;; &quot;hanasoge@...&quot; &lt;hanasoge@...&gt;; &quot;gopa292002@...&quot; &lt;g=\r\nopa292002@...&gt;; &quot;hs_sethunathan@...&quot; &lt;hs_sethunathan@...&gt;; &quot;shivashankarara=\r\no@...&quot; &lt;shivashankararao@...&gt;; &quot;sivaexpo@...&quot; &lt;sivaexpo@...&gt;; &quot;asharmanz@..=\r\n.&quot; &lt;asharmanz@...&gt;; &quot;prafulla_mendki@...&quot; &lt;prafulla_mendki@...&gt;; &quot;krishlal@=\r\n...&quot; &lt;krishlal@...&gt;; deepak &lt;deepak.gore@...&gt;; deshmukh &lt;deshmukhv@...&gt;; h =\r\n&lt;HinduCalendar@yahoogroups.com&gt;; &quot;snjoshy@...&quot; &lt;snjoshy@...&gt;; hari &lt;harimal=\r\nla@..